n-converting enzyme (ACE) in human subjects and animals[A840,A836]. ACE is a peptidyl dipeptidase that catalyzes the conversion of angiotensin I to the vasoconstrictor substance, angiotensin II[FDA Label]. Angiotensin II also stimulates aldosterone secretion by the adrenal cortex[FDA Label].', 'DrugBank', 0, 0, 0);
